## Key Findings

- 5/6 FDR-significant cancer types ROBUST (Breast, Lung, Soft Tissue, Esoph/Stomach, CNS/Brain). Pancreas MARGINAL (permutation p=0.067)
- Breast d=-1.73 is consistent but underpowered (N=8 deleted). No outliers. #1 underexplored type (~10K/yr)
- MAT2A non-dependency confirmed. 0/16 FDR-significant. Combo candidates: Head/Neck, Liver
- Pancreas weak SL explained: 11/31 intact lines also PRMT5-dependent. Not histology dilution — PRMT5 broadly needed in PDAC
- GBM QUALIFIES (25 del + 25 intact by OncotreeSubtype), d=-0.74, p=0.007. Developer pipeline missed it (grouped by Lineage not Subtype)
- Bladder TCGA-CCAT discordant (26% vs 11%). C-CAT more reliable

